rComments: Emily was great and class was interesting! Was not quite sure what to expect before the class, but ended up getting a lot out of it. Definitely had a profound impact on my perspective of the world.

Like others said, she's laid back, sometimes talks a lot, and takes a while to give you your work back. But her class is pretty easy. I learned a lot about the traveling industry and about tourism. I feel like the Ideas and Details book was useless, (since I didn't need to read it), as well as some of the activities. She likes class participation.

She's a cool person, but talks a lot.  Assignment due dates are pushed back a lot and she takes a long time to give you your work back.  It can be really easy to slack off because she is so laid back so be careful.

Great teacher! Passionate and very interesting subject: Travel in the Age of Globalization. Informative and helped us to look at travel and tourism in a new light. Wish the class was longer! Take the class, you will love it!!

Emily as a person is really cool; down-to-earth and passionate about what she teaches. But sometimes classes were boring, because it felt like she was just rambling to herself while flipping through the texts. I wish there were more student-involved discussions. Readings were okay. She's a cool instructor overall.

Emily is one of the best teachers I have ever had. She is kind, understanding, and a very knowledgeable writer herself, and her topic for Writing 1/2, Global Souls, proved to be very interesting. I only wish that the class wasn't at 8 in the morning. I really hope that she will continue to teach the class in the future.
